Fixed this warning:
```
[59/190] Compiling C object src/backend/libbaconvideowidget.a.p/bacon-video-widget.c.o
In function ‘bvw_init_video_sink’,
    inlined from ‘bacon_video_widget_realize’ at ../../../../Projects/jhbuild/totem/src/backend/bacon-video-widget.c:441:3:
../../../../Projects/jhbuild/totem/src/backend/bacon-video-widget.c:5641:20: warning: ‘glsinkbin’ may be used uninitialized [-Wmaybe-uninitialized]
 5641 |       (bvw->use_gl && !glsinkbin)) {
      |       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~^~~~~~~~~~~~~~
../../../../Projects/jhbuild/totem/src/backend/bacon-video-widget.c: In function ‘bacon_video_widget_realize’:
../../../../Projects/jhbuild/totem/src/backend/bacon-video-widget.c:5618:15: note: ‘glsinkbin’ was declared here
```

As mentioned by Jordan in https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/totem/-/merge_requests/379#note_1973779, this work-around wouldn't be needed for GTK4, and as that's still the goal for that branch, let's backport it to `gnome-43` instead.

> i would like to ask if there is a way to play dvb streams . totem is based on gstreamer that support v4l

DVB used to be supported in totem through the use of a plugin and gnome-dvb-daemon:
https://gitlab.gnome.org/Archive/gnome-dvb-daemon

gnome-dvb-daemon fell into disuse, and wasn't updated. totem still supports passing `dvb://` URLs to GStreamer, if you can figure out how to get those.
